Package: TRACLUS
Type: Package
Title: Trajectory Clustering Using Line Segments
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Martin", "Hoblisch", email = "m.hoblisch@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements the TRACLUS (TRAjectory CLUStering) algorithm by
    Lee, Han, and Whang (2007) <doi:10.1145/1247480.1247546>. The algorithm
    partitions trajectories into line segments using minimum description length
    (MDL), clusters segments via density-based spatial clustering (DBSCAN),
    and generates representative trajectories using a sweep-line algorithm.
    Supports euclidean, spherical (haversine), and equirectangular-projected
    distance calculations for geographic trajectory data.
